<br>
1) So to start, why do we care?  Reality is that people die every day.  Lots of them.  Hundreds of them even if it's a slow day.  The passing of someone we've come to know brings it home to us.  Again I will say, it's appropriate on a board about a game to lament how much we will miss these people.  It's something completely different to talk about how much someone's passing affects us when we never interacted with that person.  How many funerals went on around the world today?  How come I don't see posts about people talking about how much they will miss the former Mr. X?  How many people knew the now infamous Camillia on Innoruuk?  Wow, that many people knew someone who didn't play on this server?  How many other young women died in a similar situation in the same week?  Ah, you don't know off of the top of your head.  But yet you care and I don't if I read your responses correctly.  How many of you expressing sorrow on these posts went to the funeral or got in contact with the families?  For those who were personally involved, yeah it sucks.  And I do understand your pain.  But I didn't see anyone talking about how much they missed that person.  I just see people coming on here trying to tell me how much they care because they read some news story.  What universal truth about this am I missing?<br>
<br>
It's simple as far as I can see.  When Mr. X dies, you don't know about him.  You don't care about him (no matter how hard you pretend).  Maybe Mr. X put up with several months of excruciating pain.  But you don't know him, so you don't eulogize him.  How many innocent children went to bed battered tonight?  Well, if we don't know them, then to us they don't exist do they?  How many of you soft-hearted people hung around the cemetary today to console those who lost a loved one?  People who have no problem spending nearly every waking hour away from work playing a game on their PC's come on these boards and they're a cross between Mother Teresa and the Pope (uggh, what a picture, gonna be hard to sleep tonight, do you think a cross would be the Mother Superior as a Hermaphrodite, or the Pope with breasts?).  I never saw any of you at the funerals I went to.  Yet you expect me to break down and cry over someone that I never interacted with?  <br>
<br>
Tell me how I should care because we are human beings and I'll throw the names of those who died today in your face and ask you what you have done to ease the burden upon his or hers loved ones.  For those of you unaccustomed to loss, yes, it is hard.  But you learn to deal with it, it's not always as hard as it is at first, it will get better.  For those of you have lived it, perhaps you understand me.  I know some of you are gonna come on here and tell me what a saint you are.  Why didn't you save these people then?<br>
<br>
How many posts are there on these boards defending people being brutalized across the world, in our backyards and our neighborhoods?  Oh I see, YOU didn't know them personally.  So that makes their lives meaningless?  So that's the way it is, is it?  You care when I bring up an example, you say.  If you really cared, you wouldn't need me.  You would already care.  If the people on these boards mourning really had the love of life in their hearts, there would be no one person to mourn, they would be in mourning constantly for those who have died untimely.  But yet if I point that out I'm the heartless one.  Kill the messenger, and go back to your rose-colored world.  Who got murdered in LA or Chicago today that you cried for?  And yet somehow if I don't mourn the people you know, then I am the bad one.  <br>
<br>
I remember reading about some Internet scams where someone claimed to be dying, or had died.  They got tens of thousands of letters from people talking about how traumatized they were over it.  People talking about how they couldn't sleep or eat properly.  All over someone who didn't even exist.   <br>
<br>
There is one saying that I find appropriate here.  When we cry over someone's passing, we do not cry for them.  They are beyond feeling the pain and suffering of this world.  We cry for ourselves because we are weak and we will miss them.  But to say we are crying for the dead is a lie, because they aren't crying anymore, they are a hell of a lot better off then all of the people they left behind.  Or so they indicate at least.<br>
<br>
So go ahead and tell me &quot;Oh Ugle, you need therapy, you are such a bad person, maybe with a lot of work you can be a decent human being&quot;.  I don't see it that way.  I would like to think that I'm somewhat informed in what is really happening, and I have chosen my particular way to deal with this reality.  I criticize those people who tell me I should care more while they sit at home in front of their PC.  If you truly cared you wouldn't have time to play this game.  With all of the conflict going on in this world, this game is truly insignificant.  I'm pis sed at myself that it took this time completely away from the game with no chance of going back to realize it.  Maybe you somewhat care and do some work to help others.  But I feel confident in saying the majority of those who choose to flame me won't even do that much.  Or should I just stick my head in the sand with the majority of you?  That's the ticket, I'll just pretend that nobody is suffering anywhere in the world until it happens to someone I know, then I'll express outrage at how cruel the world is.  Nah, that would suck too.  I don't pretend to care, and my words emphasize that point.  I see too many people coming on claiming they care, and yet their (in)actions speak so loud I can't hear their words.<br>
<br>
BTW Sowl, very nice post you had, and the majority of the posts about it.  Very nicely worded, and very positive.  I remember when one of Chrisiana's family members gave me a tell in game about her passing.  I had to log immediately and couldn't play for a couple days.  It's funny how attached we can get to a virtual someone we meet.  It's not that I was never able to care, it's just that I can't care about someone I don't know, because if I did, considering the amount of death in this world, I wouldn't be able to function.  I'm sure if he had been a friend to me like he was to you Sowl I would feel differently.  <br>
<br>
But there are other threads I'm seeing inviting everyone into their pity party.  On the one hand I must say I enjoy seeing these posts.  It's like in the old days when people competed to see who could pray the loudest to prove how devout they were.  That's fallen out of favor over the last several hundred years, but it's nice to see things coming back full circle.  What was the point about starting a thread on the Innoruuk message boards about someone who didn't even play on this server?  From my jaded perspective it just looks like a way for people to come on here and tell us all how much they care.  And I must say I can't really see any coherent posts that would argue with that point of view.<br>
<br>
<br>
2) It must be nice to live in the world most of the people posting here seem to live in.  So let's be blunt.  Someone who is evil doesn't rawp someone else.  They don't have to murder someone.  Such petty displays of human lusts are signs of weakness.  And someone who is truly evil would never kill themselves because of something they have done.  Why would someone who is evil kill themselves over something that would have caused them no sorrow?  Sacrificial killings might qualify, as they were done for a purpose.  But killing someone in anger most definitely does not make the murderer truly evil.<br>
<br>
Does that make them someone who does these things a good person?  Hell no.  That makes them a wicked animal who should have vengeance poured on them in ways most people would hesitate to perform.  But does that make them evil?<br>
<br>
Read up on some of the horribly cruel people whose names have endured because of what they did.  Evil people?  Most likely not.  Petty, vindictive, cruel, hateful people most likely.  But evil?  Hardly.  If you abused a child would I consider you evil?  Do you feel a twinge at your conscience?  Then you aren't completely evil.  I might be tempted to take you out in the woods and fill the short remainder of your life with pain and suffering somewhat comparable to what you have inflicted on that innocent.  Perhaps when I have fully become I won't really care anymore.<br>
<br>
But I still do.  Hell, I still tear up when I hear the National Anthem.  I still have trouble watching &quot;Life is Beautiful&quot;.  But yet I am &quot;evil&quot; in some eyes because I don't care about someone who meant nothing to me.  True evil is not about petty pleasures of the flesh.  &quot;Goodness&quot; isn't about how much you care about poor Sally.  Goodness is someone who cares about all people AND DOES SOMETHING TO HELP THEM.  Coming on these boards talking about how much you care just makes you a mugwump.  But that's great news for the opposition, because for all of the talk and intentions, it means you haven't chosen a side.  I'm not coming on here claiming to be good, I would have no right to make that claim, even if I wanted to.  <br>
<br>
Hey, wait a minute Ugle, I'm someone who cares, you must just suck Ugle.  No, you're not.  You're someone who wants to believe they care to make themselves feel better.  But yet the majority of the posters here who comment on the people who have done these heinous acts call these people evil.  I suppose if you can go to church once a week and call yourself a religious person, then to your warped idea of absolutes those people qualify as evil.  True evil is not about petty pleasures of the flesh.  It's not about power or money.  It's about hatred of the species known as Homo Sapiens, and bringing about their downfall.  As such, the people I'm seeing on these boards being called evil fall far, far, short of that mark. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This should be fun, I had people who seemed to be frothing at the mouth telling me I needed to read Bible for myself over a post about SANTA CLAUS, so it should be fun to see the responses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/unatallia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Natallia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/16/02 11:34:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fnurt.net/~alex/pics/ebay.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ok, why do we care, and what is evil?</span><hr size=1> What was your point again?<br>
