Think of this poor girl this way.  Do we cry when someone we don't know wins the Lottery?  Do we cry when someone we don't know gets a huge raise?  Why would we feel sorrow for someone who is far, far happier now then she was a few weeks ago?  I am not condoning killing people who have problems, and think those who commit these crimes should be punished far more severely then they are.  But I can't grieve over someone who I never knew so I won't miss, and someone who's better off now then they were.  It must be awful to have that weight on your heart and mind.  Guess life sucks for you heh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uizlaaru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izlaaru</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/17/02 11:43:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/candon/izlaarusmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ok, why do we care, and what is evil?</span><hr size=1> Ugle:<br>
