<br>
If you stood by and watched someone abuse a child, and did nothing, how could you defend your actions?  I tend to be a quiet person, but have never been accused of being shy.  I might feel no emotional attachment to the person you abused.  Yet I would be unhappy about your behavior, and if it means I have to hit you so hard your clothes are out of style when you wake up, so be it.  Besides, taking someone deep into the wilderness with no witnesses around is so much more relaxing and enjoyable then in an area with lots of people around.  It can be hard to find isolated enough trails, but you'd be surprised how many private places can be found.<br>
<br>
People in stages of true grief will listen to their pain, not your arguments.  Talking to her family or friends at the funeral about why they didn't stop this before it got to this point helps nobody.  It just adds to the pain of people already emotionally shattered, which was not my intent.  If you really read my posts, my intentions were not to demean this person's life, it was meant to enrich someone else's life who perhaps you could help Oderry.  Look around at lunch for that person who always eats by themselves.  Look for that person taking yet another day off because they &quot;fell&quot; again.  The desensitizing that Gam is talking about creeps up on us.  So it's so easy to ignore the person dressed in black walking between her classes, head down, talking to nobody.  Or the guy at work who says &quot;You know, if I lost this job I would kill myself&quot;.  He's kind of tough to work with, because frankly I don't like him much, but damn, he'll sit and talk with ya for an hour if I let him.  And it shouldn't be about me, it should be about your fellow man.<br>
<br>
Besides, sure you can judge my feelings.  Does that give you the right to criticize them?  If you feel comfortable doing so.  I have opinions, and so do you.  Mine are no more valuable, even to me, then yours are.  But I believe in my opinion, so you'd have to convince me with yours why you were right.<br>
<br>
I can say with absolute surety that I would not give my condolences to her family.  I might agree that it was a pretty crappy situation.  But for all I know, the person I'm talking to used to beat or abuse her as well.  Hell, for all I know Oderry you used to abuse her.  For all I know Salitana helped him murder his daughter and then turned the gun on him and made it look like a suicide.  And since I didn't know this girl, how can I talk about what she meant to me?  It would be crocodile tears like those I saw that inspired me to make my post.<br>
<br>
<br>
