<br>
So when I'm in basic training I get a letter from my former boss with a newspaper clipping about my former co-worker.  He had been caught (again) molesting children, his &quot;wife&quot; wasn't, and the house was a rental.  We all worked with this guy for well over a year buying his nice little stories.  Only to find out he was one of the lower forms of life.  If I ever ran into him on the street I would express my displeasure with him, hopefully not enough to get me thrown in jail for more then a couple weeks or so.<br>
<br>
So I try to be a little more aware now.  You know what they say, fool me once - shame on you, fool me twice - shame on me.  I think to myself, if I had gotten to know this guy better perhaps I could have seen more into his psyche and saved this poor little girl from what she went through.  I don't blame myself for what he did, he did it.  But I do carry the feeling around that maybe if I had done a little more........   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uunfetered.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unfetered</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/17/02 8:55:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ok, why do we care, and what is evil?</span><hr size=1> Ugle may I ask you this?<br>
